                Carbobdale, Illinois
                October 6, 1971
                Hon. John G. Neihardt
                Columbia, Missouri 
                Dear Gaki, 
                It was great to read of you in this evenings St. Louis Post-Dispatch....(October 5, 1971)
                Have pleasant memories of my visit with you several years ago while returning from a western trip. 
                Have not done much writing of late as Dee Brown &amp; Vine Deloria have coveredthings real well in their books. 
                I would like to see my books come out in paperback, especially Broken Peace Pipes &amp; Red Men of Fire. One of my books The Unconquered Seminole Indians which was a paperback has now passed the half mililon mark. 
                My most recent work has been the discovery of the first fort De Charters 1719-27 in Randolph County, Illinois. As a result of this find Illinois has purchased almost two thousand acres surrounding it. 
                Again Congratulations on your achievements...they have been great.... 
                Sincerely, 
                    <signed>Irvin M. Peithmann</signed> 
                Irvin M. Peithmann 
                
                <fw>2</fw>
                
            </div1>
